1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the ergodic capacity of a communication system, which is a fundamental concept in information theory. 
2. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) - The paper focuses on a dual-hop relaying system, which is a common technique used in communication and networking. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with a wireless communication system, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper analyzes the performance of a communication system, which can be viewed as a control system. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper considers multipath fading, which is a common phenomenon in wireless multimedia communication.
